{"type":"turn_end","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We need to decide: vote demonstrated or not_demonstrated based on the record. The proposition: \"Before January 1, 2027 at 00:00 PST, Polymarket launched an official fungible token: a fungible token officially released by Polymarket and publicly communicated through official Polymarket channels, excluding NFT launches, promotional offerings, tokenized point systems, and token launches in collaboration with other projects or communities.\"\n\nWe have evidence: pUSD is an ERC-20 token, official Polymarket docs describe it as collateral token, publicly communicated via changelog, Help Center, etc., launched April 28, 2026 (before deadline). Exclusions: not NFT, not promotional offering, not tokenized point system, not collaboration launch. The defense argues that collateral token is not an \"official token launch\" but the proposition's definition does not exclude collateral tokens. The plaintiff argues that under the given definition, pUSD qualifies.\n\nWe need to weigh preponderance. The admitted record includes official Polymarket documentation describing pUSD as collateral token, but also says it's officially released by Polymarket and publicly communicated. The definition does not require governance rights or airdrop. So likely the proposition is demonstrated.\n\nThus vote demonstrated with rationale: The admitted record shows pUSD is a fungible ERC-20 token officially released by Polymarket via official channels (documentation, changelog, Help Center) before the deadline, and does not fall under any exclusion.\n\nWe'll call submit_council_vote.\n\nBut we should maybe first check the record via get_case to ensure we have the latest? Already we have the prompt and record. However we could call aar_get_case to confirm. But not necessary. We'll just submit vote.\n\nWe must call mcp with tool aar_submit_council_vote and args JSON string.\n\nLet's do that.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f5aa44b457f84d788572cdaa","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\": \"demonstrated\", \"rationale\": \"The admitted record shows pUSD is a fungible ERC-20 token officially released by Polymarket via official documentation, changelog, and Help Center before the deadline, and it is not an NFT, promotional offering, tokenized point system, or collaboration launch.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":18044,"output":513,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":18557,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782806376142,"responseId":"gen-1782806376-VuygftAdpgyuNcHNElym","responseModel":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b-20230311"},"toolResults":[{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_f5aa44b457f84d788572cdaa","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex10-20260630073904\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 809294\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex10-20260630073904\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T08:14:15.691656518Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C4\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":809294,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":12}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C4\ncase_id: arb-ex10-20260630073904\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C4\nremaining_ms: 809294\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex10-20260630073904\",\"member_id\":\"C4\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remai